es of poor Muslim women as backward, subservient, oppressed, and in need of saving.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 10. Jan 2022) 0aNon-governmental organizationszBangladesh. 0aRural womenzBangladeshxSocial conditions. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aBangladesh, women's issues, NGOs, village, public policy, Rural Bangladesh, Asian Studies, grassroots organization, oppression, women's mobilization programs, Polli Shomaj, social relationships, South Asia, women in South Asia.40uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978197881648040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781978816480423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781978816480/original  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK